                                <h2 class="global-heading1" id="mba-program">About IBA</h2>
								
								
								<div class="align-right about-mob">
									<img class="" src="images/aboutmba.jpg" alt="Mentorship">
								</div>
                                <p>Wharton School of the University of Pennsylvania and the University of Karachi set up the Institute of Public and Business Administration in 1955 with the mission to create managerial capital and leadership for the industry of Pakistan. The institute introduced two graduate degree programs in Pakistan, namely, Master of Public Administration in 1955 and Master of Business Administration (MBA) in 1956. Since then, more than 8000 people have graduated MBA from IBA, many becoming prominent leaders, including the President of Pakistan (Mr. Mamnoon Hussain), Prime Minister of Pakistan (Mr. Shaukat Aziz), and members of top management teams in national and international business enterprises.</p>
								<p> IBA became a degree-awarding institution in 1994 by the charter of the Sind Assembly. To manage its organic growth as a university having approximately 5000 students, IBA divisionalized in 2021 by establishing three autonomous and independent schools, namely, the School of Business Studies (SBS), the School of Economics and Social Sciences (SESS), and the School of Mathematics and Computer Science (SMCS). </p>
								<p> The MBA program is now part of the portfolio of the SBS and managed through the Directorate of MBA and EMBA. </p>
								
								<div class="align-right mobile">
									<img class="" src="images/aboutmba.jpg" alt="Mentorship">
								</div>
								
								<div class="center-sec">							
								<p style="font-size: 19px;text-align: left;"><strong class="bold-global">Learn More</strong></p>
									<div class="more-news">
									<a href="https://www.iba.edu.pk/history.php" target="_blank"> About IBA </a>
									<a href="https://sbs.iba.edu.pk/overview.php" target="_blank">About SBS  </a>
									</div>							
								</div>
								
								
								 <div class="spacer"> </div>
								 <h2 class="global-heading1" id="mba-iba">The IBA MBA </h2>
								<div class="align-right mba-iba">
									<img class="" src="images/about1.jpg" alt="Mentorship">
								</div>
									
							<p>Since 1956, the MBA has been the legacy and flagship program of IBA. The current MBA is a two-year, full-time, rigorous master's program in business administration designed  for rising professionals with 3-8 years of experience who are positioned to advance into strategic management roles. 
							 It serves as an accelerator for ambitious individuals transitioning from technical expertise to management leadership, from individual contribution to team leadership, from functional specialization to general management. </p>

							<p> The program equips you with the knowledge, analytical frameworks, and leadership capabilities essential for advancing your career in Pakistan's most dynamic organizations.
							  You'll develop proficiency in key business disciplines, analytical decision-making, ethical leadership and teamwork, effective communication, and strategic use of technology in management. 
							  This comprehensive skill set positions you among the next generation of leaders shaping Pakistan's corporate future.
							</p>

							<p>
							  The MBA is not just a degree—it is professional transformation that accelerates your journey from functional expertise to strategic leadership 
							  Joining the MBA means becoming part of an ever-growing community of professionals committed to driving innovation, enhancing organizational competitiveness, and increasing the productivity of Pakistan's economy.
							</p>

							<p>
							  The MBA has been designed using the benchmarks of leading business schools worldwide. 
							  IBA introduced the MBA to Pakistan in 1956, establishing the standard by which all MBA programs in the country are measured.
							  The AACSB accreditation is international acknowledgment that the program has been rigorously evaluated and meets world-class standards. 
							  It is a testament that the MBA not only has the legacy of pioneers but also holds the currency of leaders.
							</p>

							<p>
							  The MBA at IBA develops the whole professional through an eclectic mix of pedagogical methods including the case method, problem-based learning, and experiential engagement.
							  The program is built around the DRIVEN framework—Discipline, Reason, Integrity, Value-Added impact, Excellence, and Nobility—while developing your Technical, Intellectual, Emotional, and Social capabilities (TIES). 
							  This dual framework ensures you develop both the analytical rigor and the leadership maturity required for strategic management positions.
							</p>

							<p>
							  IBA provides financial assistance to eligible students through various sources including need-based aid, merit-based scholarships, and corporate sponsorships. 
							  For financing options available at IBA, please see 
							  <a href="https://www.iba.edu.pk/financialassistance/" target="_blank">Financial Assistance at IBA</a>.
							</p>
								<!--------------The DRIVEN MBA---->
							<div class="spacer3"> </div>
								<h2 class="global-heading1" id="program-structure">The DRIVEN MBA</h2>
								<div class="align-right mba-iba">
									<img class="" src="images/thumb-driven-section.jpg" alt="The DRIVEN MBA">
								</div>
								<p>What separates professionals who advance rapidly into strategic management from those who remain in functional roles? Over seven decades of developing Pakistan's business talent, we've identified six dimensions of professional excellence that consistently predict career success. These aren't personality traits you're born with—they're capabilities you can develop. This is DRIVEN.</p>
								<div style="max-width: 90%; margin: 0 auto;">
									<p><strong>D: DISCIPLINE - <em style="font-style: italic;">Building Systems That Scale</em></strong></p>
									<p>Rising professionals often succeed through personal effort and individual brilliance. Strategic managers succeed by creating systems that work beyond their direct involvement. <strong>Discipline</strong> is the capacity to architect processes, frameworks, and structures that scale—transforming personal excellence into organizational capability. It's the difference between being indispensable because you do everything yourself, and being invaluable because you build things that work without you.</p>
								</div>
								<div style="max-width: 90%; margin: 0 auto;">
									<p><strong>R: REASON - <em style="font-style: italic;">Strategic Thinking Under Complexity</em></strong></p>
									<p>As you advance from functional roles to strategic positions, problems become more ambiguous and decisions carry greater consequences with incomplete information. <strong>Reason</strong> is the analytical rigor and strategic judgment to cut through complexity, identify what truly matters, and make decisions that create compounding value over time. It's moving from "what should I do today?" to "what needs to be true three years from now?"</p>
								</div>
								<div style="max-width: 90%; margin: 0 auto;">
									<p><strong>I: INTEGRITY - <em style="font-style: italic;">Building Trust-Based Influence</em></strong></p>
									<p>Individual contributors deliver results through technical skill. Strategic managers deliver results through influence across teams and functions they don't directly control. <strong>Integrity</strong> is the foundation of professional credibility—the ethical consistency that allows you to build the trust necessary to lead teams, influence peers, and earn the confidence of senior leadership. In competitive markets, your reputation becomes your most valuable asset.</p>
								</div>
								<div style="max-width: 90%; margin: 0 auto;">
									<p><strong>V: VALUE ADDED - <em style="font-style: italic;"> Creating Measurable Professional Value</em></strong></p>
									<p>Every career transition requires demonstrating that you can create value at the next level. <strong>Value-Added</strong> impact is the capability to identify opportunities, apply strategic frameworks, and deliver measurable results that justify your advancement—proving you're ready for greater responsibility through tangible contributions. It's understanding that "doing your job well" maintains your position, but "creating new value" earns you the next one.</p>
								</div>
								<div style="max-width: 90%; margin: 0 auto;">
									<p><strong>E: EXCELLENCE - <em style="font-style: italic;"> Execution Standards That Open Doors</em></strong></p>
									<p>In competitive professional markets, "good enough" isn't enough. <strong>Excellence</strong> is the commitment to execution quality that rivals the world's best organizations—the standard of work that gets you noticed, recommended, and considered for strategic opportunities. It's the difference between being competent and being invaluable. Excellence isn't perfection—it's the consistent delivery of work that exceeds expectations.</p>
								</div>
								<div style="max-width: 90%; margin: 0 auto;">
									<p><strong>N: NOBILITY - <em style="font-style: italic;"> Leading with Purpose Beyond Personal Gain</em></strong></p>
									<p>The most successful professionals understand that career advancement isn't about climbing over others—it's about lifting others while rising yourself. <strong>Nobility</strong> is leadership with a service mindset, recognizing that the professionals who create value for their organizations, develop their teams, and contribute to their industries build the most sustainable and meaningful careers. It's understanding that the best way to advance is to make everyone around you better.</p>
								</div>
								<p><strong style="font-style: italic;">TIES of Operational Capabilities</strong></p>
								<p>While DRIVEN provides the values foundation for professional excellence, TIES represents the operational skill set you develop through the MBA:</p>
								<ul class="list-global">
									<li><strong>Technical expertise:</strong> Functional and analytical capabilities across business disciplines</li>
									<li><strong>Intellectual agility:</strong> Critical thinking, strategic reasoning, and adaptive learning</li>
									<li><strong>Emotional intelligence:</strong> Self-awareness, resilience, and relationship management</li>
									<li><strong>Social effectiveness:</strong> Communication, collaboration, and stakeholder influence</li>
								</ul>
								<p>DRIVEN guides how you develop and apply your TIES:</p>
								<ul class="list-global">
									<li><strong>Discipline</strong> shapes how you use <strong>Technical</strong> skills (building scalable processes, not one-off solutions)</li>
									<li><strong>Reason</strong> enhances your <strong>Intellectual</strong> agility (strategic thinking, not just problem-solving)</li>
									<li><strong>Integrity</strong> strengthens your <strong>Emotional</strong> intelligence (authentic leadership, not manipulation)</li>
									<li><strong>Value-Added</strong> focus directs your <strong>Social</strong> effectiveness (measurable impact, not just networking)</li>
									<li><strong>Excellence</strong> elevates all capabilities to world-class standards</li>
									<li><strong>Nobility</strong> ensures your capabilities serve purposes beyond personal advancement</li>
								</ul>
								<p><strong style="font-style: italic;">Why DRIVEN Matters in MBA?</strong></p>
								<p>The MBA at IBA isn't just about acquiring business knowledge—thousands of programs offer that. We develop DRIVEN professionals who apply knowledge with discipline, think strategically under complexity, build influence through integrity, create measurable value, maintain world-class execution standards, and lead with purpose.</p>
								<p>This framework isn't abstract philosophy. It's the practical distinction between professionals who advance rapidly into strategic leadership and those who remain technically competent but career-constrained.</p>
								<p><strong>If you recognize that your career acceleration depends not just on what you know, but on how you think, work, and lead—you're ready for the IBA MBA.</strong></p>
