								<h2 class="global-heading1" id="program-structure">Program Structure </h2>	
													
								<p>The MBA has been carefully designed to accelerate the transition of rising professionals from functional expertise to strategic management positions in Pakistan's most dynamic organizations. The program develops a comprehensive set of Technical, Intellectual, Emotional, and Social capabilities (TIES) guided by the DRIVEN framework of Discipline, Reason, Integrity, Value-Added impact, Excellence, and Nobility—the essential competencies that distinguish professionals who advance into strategic leadership from those who remain in functional roles.</p>

								<p>Additionally, the program provides the foundation and qualification to study beyond the MBA, if you choose to do so. The MBA is an accredited qualification of Level-7 in accordance with the National Qualification Framework of Pakistan (NQFP), enabling graduates to proceed directly to doctoral programs.</p>

								<p>The program requires the completion of 60 Credit Hours in accordance with NQFP, spread over two years of full-time study. The core of the program comprises more than half of the total Credit Hours and covers rigorous scientific knowledge pertaining to business disciplines, economics, organizational behavior, and quantitative analysis. The first year is dedicated to building this comprehensive foundation through academic and experiential training.</p>

								<p>By the completion of the first year, you will be well-versed in how organizations function strategically and ready to develop a personalized portfolio of expertise. During the second year, you will build your specialized knowledge by choosing from a carefully curated menu of elective courses aligned with your career trajectory. Additionally, you will engage in experiential interactions with our partner enterprises and undertake the MBA Capstone Project, applying your strategic frameworks to solve a significant real-world business challenge.</p>

								<p>Overall, the MBA will equip you with the following strategic management competencies:</p>

								
								<ul class="list-global">
								<li style="list-style: none;padding-right: 180px">
									<strong><em style="font-style: italic;font-size: 17px;">
										Knowledge of Business and Management: </em></strong>
									
									You will develop the ability to analyze how organizations create value, compete in markets, and navigate complex local and global environments—essential for strategic management roles. </li>
									
								<li style="list-style: none;padding-right: 180px">
								<strong><em style="font-style: italic;font-size: 17px;">
									Analytical Decision Making:  </em> </strong>	
									
									You will learn the science and art of making rational decisions under conditions of complexity and uncertainty, and implementing them effectively across organizational levels. </li>
								<li style="list-style: none;padding-right: 180px">
								<strong><em style="font-style: italic;font-size: 17px;">
									Ethical Leadership and Teamwork:   </em></strong>
								You will develop the ability to lead teams, build cross-functional collaboration, and influence stakeholders—critical capabilities for advancing beyond individual contribution. </li>					
									
								<li style="list-style: none;padding-right: 180px">
								<strong><em style="font-style: italic;font-size: 17px;">
									Effective Communication: </em> </strong>
								You will develop the ability to communicate strategic ideas persuasively to diverse audiences, from technical teams to senior leadership. </li>		
									
									
									
								<li style="list-style: none;padding-right: 180px">
								<strong><em style="font-style: italic;font-size: 17px;">
									Technology-Enabled Management: </em>	</strong>
								You will learn how modern technologies and tools can be harnessed to drive organizational efficiency, innovation, and competitive advantage. </li>								
								</ul>
								
								<p> In summary, the MBA provides a unique blend of rigorous academic training and practical application that accelerates your advancement into strategic management positions in medium and large business enterprises. </p>
								
								
