									<h2 class="global-heading1" id="admission">Admission</h2>	
								<p>Candidates for MBA are considered eligible for admission if they have earned an undergraduate degree (equivalent to 16 years of education) from an HEC-recognized university with a CGPA of 2.5 or higher, and possess a minimum of 3 years of post-qualification professional experience.</p>
								<p>The MBA is designed for rising professionals with 3-8 years of experience who are positioned to advance into strategic management roles. We take great pride in providing personalized attention to the development of each student. Accordingly, we select a small, highly competitive cohort every year. We seek ambitious individuals who demonstrate the attitude, aptitude, and professional trajectory to advance into strategic leadership positions. </p>
								<p>We encourage you to carefully assess your career stage and aspirations before applying for admission. Our screening and selection process is highly competitive, rigorous, and selective. We believe in diversity and inclusivity and use academic and professional merit as the only criteria for selection based on evidence related to the following:</p>

