					<h3 id="faqs">FAQs </h3><div class="spacer"></div>
						
					<strong class="faq-category">Program Overview & General Information</strong>
					
					
					
					<button class="accordion1">What is the difference between MBA and Executive MBA? </button>
					<div class="panel" style=""><br>
							<div style="overflow-x:auto;">
						<p> The MBA is designed for rising professionals with 3-8 years of experience who are transitioning into strategic management roles. The Executive MBA (EMBA) serves established executives with 10-20 years of experience, including minimum 5 years in management and leadership positions, who are focused on institutional transformation and senior leadership development. </p>
								<p> Key Differences:</p>
								<ul class="list-global">
								<li>Experience Requirement: MBA requires 3–8 years; EMBA requires 10–20 years</li>
								<li>Career Stage: MBA serves rising professionals; EMBA serves established executives</li>
								<li>Program Focus: MBA emphasizes career acceleration and professional transformation; EMBA emphasizes leadership transformation and institutional impact</li>
								<li>Schedule: MBA is full-time (weekday); EMBA is weekend-based (alternate Saturdays–Sundays)</li>
								<li>Duration: Both programs are 2 years</li>

								</ul>		
						</div>
					</div>
					
					<button class="accordion1">I have 10+ years of experience. Should I apply for MBA or EMBA? </button>
					<div class="panel" style=""><br>
							<div style="overflow-x:auto;">
						<p>With 10+ years of experience, the Executive MBA is likely the better fit, especially if you hold management or leadership positions. The EMBA is specifically designed for established executives focused on strategic leadership transformation and institutional impact. Contact our admissions team at <a href="mailto:emba.info@iba.edu.pk">emba.info@iba.edu.pk</a> to discuss your specific situation.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					
					
					<button class="accordion1"> I have only 2 years of experience. Can I still apply? </button>
					<div class="panel" style=""><br>
							<div style="overflow-x:auto;">
						<p> No. The minimum requirement is 3 years of post-qualification professional experience. This requirement ensures that all participants have sufficient professional context to engage meaningfully with business and management cases and contribute to peer learning. </p>
						</div>
					</div>
					
					
					<button class="accordion1"> What is the typical profile of MBA students? </button>
					<div class="panel" style=""><br>
							<div style="overflow-x:auto;">
						<p> MBA students are rising professionals, typically aged 25-35, with 3-8 years of professional experience across diverse industries including finance, technology, manufacturing, consulting, healthcare, and entrepreneurship. They are positioned at career inflection points, ready to transition from functional expertise to strategic management roles. </p>
						</div>
					</div>
					
					
					
					
					
					
					
					<button class="accordion1">What is the role of NQFP and HEC in MBA?</button>
					<div class="panel" style=""><br>
							<div style="overflow-x:auto;">
						<p>The academic status/level of all academic degrees is assessed in relation to the National Qualification Framework of Pakistan (NQFP). The Higher Education Commission (HEC) is a constitutional institution that has the exclusive authority to assess and certify whether an academic program of a university and its degree is legitimate and has a certain level of qualification according to the national and international standards. The MBA conforms to the NQFP qualification of Level 7 and is accredited by the HEC as a qualification equivalent to 18 years of formal education in Pakistan.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<button class="accordion1">Is MBA a full-time program?</button>
					<div class="panel" style=""><br>
							<div style="overflow-x:auto;">
						<p> Yes. In line with the HEC guidelines, we require our students to take a minimum of 9 credit hours in a semester and complete the program within a maximum period of 4 years. Total program credits are equally divided over four semesters. Students successfully completing the prescribed courses in every semester comfortably complete the program in 2 years. To accommodate diverse needs of our students, classes will be typically scheduled during the first four days of the week in the first half of the day, except for Wednesday, which is a full-day schedule for classes between 9 a.m. to 5 p.m.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<button class="accordion1">How many rounds of MBA admission are there in a year?</button>
					<div class="panel" style=""><br>
							<div style="overflow-x:auto;">
						<p> MBA admissions are offered only once a year for the fall intake as part of a single round of admissions for the Fall semester intake. Application cycle typically begins in January and ends in April every year.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<strong class="faq-category">Eligibility & Academic Background</strong>
					<button class="accordion1">What are the eligibility criteria for applicants holding foreign degrees?</button>
					<div class="panel" style=""><br>
							<div style="overflow-x:auto;">
						<p>All foreign degree holders need to obtain equivalence certificate from Higher Education Commission of Pakistan. Foreign qualification must be equivalent to a degree involving 16-years of education in Pakistan.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<button class="accordion1">What are the eligibility requirements for applicants holding professional qualifications such as CA/ACCA?</button>
					<div class="panel" style=""><br>
							<div style="overflow-x:auto;">
						<p>According to HEC, professional certificates of qualification issued by ICMAP, ICAP, and membership of ACCA are equivalent to 16 years of education in Pakistan. Therefore, holders of are these qualifications are eligible for admission in MBA provided that they have 3 years of experience after the date of completion of any of these qualifications.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<button class="accordion1">I already have an MBA. Can I apply for the MBA?</button>
					<div class="panel" style=""><br>
							<div style="overflow-x:auto;">
						<p>Yes.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<button class="accordion1">I have already completed some courses of MBA elsewhere. Can I transfer my admission or credits to the MBA?</button>
					<div class="panel" style=""><br>
							<div style="overflow-x:auto;">
						<p>No. You must be admitted to the program through the required admission process and start the program afresh.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<strong class="faq-category">Professional Experience</strong>
					<button class="accordion1">How important is professional experience in the admission process? </button>
					<div class="panel" style=""><br>
							<div style="overflow-x:auto;">
						<p>Starting 2025, IBA requires 3 years of post-qualification experience. </p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<button class="accordion1">What does post-qualification experience mean and how important is it in admission?</button>
					<div class="panel" style=""><br>
							<div style="overflow-x:auto;">
						<p>The candidate for MBA must have earned at least 3 years of professional work experience after the completion of their undergraduate degree. Part-time experience during education does not count. This requirement is one of the key eligibility conditions for the program and must be met.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<strong class="faq-category">Testing & Application Process</strong>
					<button class="accordion1">What is the process of admission into MBA?</button>
					<div class="panel" style=""><br>
							<div style="overflow-x:auto;">
						<p>Please consult the admission schedule as a first step. You'll need to create an online account to access the application form. You can fill in the application form, attach documents required for each component, save the application, and submit the completed application by the deadline. Please note that incomplete and duplicate applications are rejected without any notice to the applicant.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<button class="accordion1">Is entrance test necessary for admission to the MBA?</button>
					<div class="panel" style=""><br>
							<div style="overflow-x:auto;">
						<p>Yes. We take IBA Aptitude Test for admission. Alternatively, we can accept Graduate Management Admission Test (GMAT) or Graduate Record Examination (GRE) test scores which are not older than two years.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<button class="accordion1">What is the current pattern of the MBA aptitude test?</button>
					<div class="panel" style=""><br>
							<div style="overflow-x:auto;">
						<p>Admission test is designed along the lines of GMAT to assess reading comprehension, critical thinking, quantitative reasoning, verbal reasoning, and essay writing.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<button class="accordion1">What is the minimum GMAT/GRE score requirement for admission?</button>
					<div class="panel" style=""><br>
							<div style="overflow-x:auto;">
						<p>For GMAT, the minimum score is 600 and for GRE, a minimum of 160 in quantitative and 150 in verbal part is required. Please note that these scores represent only a minimum eligibility condition and do not reflect the qualification merit for admission.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<button class="accordion1">Who is a referee and how many referees do I need?</button>
					<div class="panel" style=""><br>
							<div style="overflow-x:auto;">
						<p>A referee is a person who can give a valid opinion about your academic and leadership potential. We need two referees whom we can contact on your behalf and who are willing to provide us with the required information about you.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<button class="accordion1">What is the Business Orientation Program (BOP) and who needs it?</button>
					<div class="panel" style=""><br>
							<div style="overflow-x:auto;">
						<p>The BOP is an intensive and graded program of four weeks in which all the participants are primed to the philosophy and strategy of the MBA program, provided with relevant knowledge and skills to be able to relate to its content, and coached in the appropriate attitudes and behaviors needed to successfully complete it. The BOP puts all the participants, regardless of their academic and professional background, on an equal footing so that no one has any disadvantage in terms of academic know-how and intellectual skills relative to their peers in the cohort. Accordingly, all participants regardless of their undergraduate degree are required to attend and pass the BOP to pursue the program. Participants failing the BOP are dropped from the program.
							</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<strong class="faq-category">Selection & Interview</strong>	
					<button class="accordion1">Do you invite all candidates for the Aptitude Test?</button>
					<div class="panel" style=""><br>
							<div style="overflow-x:auto;">
						<p>No. We invite only those candidates for the Aptitude Test who meet the eligibility criteria. </p>
						</div>
					</div>
				
					<button class="accordion1">Do you invite all candidates appearing in the Aptitude Test for an interview? </button>
					<div class="panel" style=""><br>
							<div style="overflow-x:auto;">
						<p>No. We invite only those candidates who demonstrate a reasonable potential to be successful in the program by achieving a reasonable score in the Aptitude Test. </p>
						</div>
					</div>	
					<strong class="faq-category">Post-Decision & Reapplication</strong>		
					<button class="accordion1">If my application is not successful, can I apply again? </button>
					<div class="panel" style=""><br>
							<div style="overflow-x:auto;">
						<p>Yes. You can apply in the future rounds of admission, but you will have to apply afresh. We do not consider previous applications as the input for admission.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				
			</div>
